**Findings**

1. [P1] Delete action is UI-only at [testpage.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L48C1) - `handleDelete` only removes the row from local state. The item comes back on the next fetch/reload, and delete failures can never be surfaced. FIX: use a real async DELETE flow and only finalize removal on success.

2. [P2] Retry requests are not cleaned up on unmount at [testpage.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L34C1) and [testpage.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L41C1) - retries replace `abortRef.current`, but the effect cleanup still aborts only the first controller. A retry can outlive the component and still hit state setters after unmount. FIX: abort the latest controller from cleanup and guard post-fetch updates.

3. [P2] Partially invalid payloads are hidden as an empty state at [testpage.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx#L22C1) - the code only verifies that the response is an array, then silently filters bad rows. Broken API data can therefore look like a normal “no items” result instead of an error. FIX: validate row shape and fail into error state when required fields are missing.

